%% Data Flow Diagram for vllm-gaudi
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6
sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as Data Science Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant RBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant VLLM as vLLM API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant HPU as Intel Gaudi HPU<br/>PCIe/SynapseAI
    participant S3 as Model Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant HF as Hugging Face Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant HPU2 as HPU Workers (rank 1..N)<br/>HCCL/TCP
    participant Decode as Decode Instance<br/>NIXL/RDMA

    Note over Client,HPU: Flow 1: Model Inference Request (External)
    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Gateway->>RBAC: Forward (HTTPS/8443)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SAR)
    RBAC->>VLLM: Forward (HTTP/8000)<br/>plaintext (localhost)
    VLLM->>HPU: Execute inference<br/>PCIe/SynapseAI Device I/O
    HPU-->>VLLM: Inference result
    VLLM-->>RBAC: JSON Response
    RBAC-->>Gateway: JSON Response
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response

    Note over VLLM,HF: Flow 2: Model Loading at Startup
    VLLM->>S3: Download model weights<br/>Auth: IAM / ServiceAccount
    S3-->>VLLM: Model artifacts
    VLLM->>HF: Download tokenizer/config<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (optional)
    HF-->>VLLM: Tokenizer files
    VLLM->>HPU: Load model to HPU memory<br/>PCIe/SynapseAI Device I/O

    Note over HPU,HPU2: Flow 3: Distributed Multi-HPU Inference
    HPU->>HPU2: HCCL all-reduce/all-gather<br/>Dynamic port, plaintext
    HPU2-->>HPU: Collective results

    Note over VLLM,Decode: Flow 4: Disaggregated Prefill-Decode (NIXL)
    VLLM->>Decode: KV-cache transfer<br/>NIXL/RDMA, plaintext
    Decode-->>VLLM: Transfer acknowledgement
